{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EDTYRmWkXeRNq3beieHiAy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`/tmp/test-ca.key` matches the CA cert in the `test-ca` configmap. Now I can generate a new valid TLS certificate for `demo.example.com` signed by this CA, and update the `expired-tls-secret` with the new cert and key.\n\nThe leaf.cnf is in the openssl-toolbox pod at `/tmp/leaf.cnf`. I can either:\n1. Generate the cert locally on the host using openssl (since openssl is available at `/tmp/`)\n2. Use the openssl-toolbox pod\n\nLet me generate the cert on the host since I have the CA key there. I'll:\n1. Create a new private key for demo.example.com\n2. Generate a CSR using a config with the proper SAN\n3. Sign it with the Test CA\n4. Update the `expired-tls-secret` with the new cert and key\n\nI can create the config inline rather than relying on what's in the pod, then use the CA key and certificate I already have.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":369,"cache_read_input_tokens":44030,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":369},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9888cb03-f287-461e-ba1f-bf42acb0c783","uuid":"6607b7b7-e0f2-4347-9426-0cef0df1e164","request_id":"req_011CcakKdof8R3paE6u5Ydky"}
